		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This research proposal is he direct continuation of my past activity at the Department of Mathematical Sciences in Durham.  With the important help of experts of that Department, I found, in collaboration with another author, two different approaches to classical null-vectors in 2D Integrable Field Theories.  The first make use of the integrable flows and some special fields.  The second is based on a new Virasoro-like symmetry.  From the pattern of Conformal Field Theories it is known that the presence of null-vectors allows to write equations for Correlation Functions.  The proposal consists both in the quantisation of classical methods and in searching for equations constraining the Correlation functions.  More specifically, in order of priority:1a) quantisation of generators of the Virasoro-like algebra;1b) investigation of null-vectors in the quantised algebra;1c) derivation of equations for the Correlation Functions;2a) quantisation of null-vector arising in the first method;2b) derivation of equations for the Correlation Functions.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
